description: This is a Hero Illustrated special, detailing a Who's Who of super heroes from different publishers. Along with Superman, Batman, Spider-Man and The Spirit, are The Crow, Spawn and Swamp Thing; and newcomers Hellboy, The Mask and X. This is a prime snapshot of super hero comics of the 1990's, and most notably, the mid-'90's. Characters are not just drawn from the four main publishers, Dark Horse, DC, Image and Marvel, but from smaller publishers like Defiant, Kitchen Sink and independent publishers as well. Also of note is that there are only three teams featured in this Who' Who - the Fantastic Four, the X-Men and WildC.A.T.s. Noteworthy for their absence are equally enduring teams like the Justice League, The Avengers and Teen Titans. It is interesting to flip through and wonder what became of predicted future stars like Ax, cover duo Black and White and Lorca, as well as the publishing houses they were from.
name: Comic Book Who's Who
